MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION : Sections from the lung show an infiltrating halfway differentiated squamous cell carcinoma .
The tumor infiltrates a segmental bronchus , has penetrated it and ulcerated the mucosa .
It is compressing the segmental artery which is not infiltrated by the tumor .
There are 5 para ~ arterial lymph nodes , one of which shows metastatic tumor .
